From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-13] Opt-in tool_call_format="json" (Hermes JSON tool calls)

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (shipped default stack:
Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 + Q3.6-5 + Q3.6-6 + Q3.6-12)

Status: OPT-IN. This patch ships but is NOT applied to the default
patched/35B-A3B.jinja. The native Qwen XML tool-call format
(<function=...>/<parameter=...>) is the model's training distribution and
is what Qwen-native parsers (vLLM qwen3_coder / qwen3_xml) expect. Apply
this only for a deployment stuck on a Hermes-JSON-only engine.

What it does: adds a `tool_call_format` kwarg (default "xml"). When set to
"json", (a) the tool-instruction example + the <IMPORTANT> format bullet
describe a single JSON object with "name"/"arguments" keys inside
<tool_call></tool_call>, and (b) each assistant tool call serializes as
`<tool_call>\n{"name": ..., "arguments": {...}}\n</tool_call>` instead of
the XML <function=>/<parameter=> nesting. Mapping arguments are emitted via
`| tojson`; non-empty string-form arguments pass through trimmed; missing,
none, or whitespace-only arguments become `{}` (so the emitted object is
always valid JSON).

Default path unchanged: with the kwarg unset or "xml", the render is
byte-identical to the pre-Q3.6-13 shipped template — verified across
single / parallel / string-args tool calls and the tool-instruction block
(see tests test_q36_13_*).

Why opt-in, not shipped by default: froggeric's own v21.1 changelog records
that it REVERTED an earlier JSON-default experiment because "JSON
fundamentally broke vLLM's native qwen3_coder parser." Shipping JSON by
default would degrade the dominant parser path. Unlike Q3.6-11 (payload
truncation) this is NOT lossy — the same arguments are re-serialized in a
different grammar and it is default-off — which is why it ships as an
applyable .patch (like Q3.6-9 / Q3.6-10) rather than being catalog-only.

Prior art: froggeric Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates v21.3, snapshotted at
docs/sources/hf-snapshots/froggeric-Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates-v21.3.jinja.
This port trims whitespace-only string args to {} (froggeric's form emits
them raw, producing invalid JSON). Diffs against the shipped default stack
(through Q3.6-12).

--- a/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
+++ b/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+{%- set _tool_format = tool_call_format if tool_call_format is defined else 'xml' %}
 {%- set image_count = namespace(value=0) %}
 {%- set video_count = namespace(value=0) %}
 {%- macro render_content(content, do_vision_count, is_system_content=false) %}
@@ -84,7 +85,12 @@
         {{- tool | tojson }}
     {%- endfor %}
     {{- "\n</tools>" }}
+    {#- Q3.6-13 (opt-in): switch the tool-instruction example + <IMPORTANT> bullet to Hermes JSON when tool_call_format=='json'; XML (native) is the default and is byte-identical to the pre-Q3.6-13 state. -#}
+    {%- if _tool_format == 'json' %}
+    {{- '\n\nIf you choose to call a function ONLY reply in the following format with NO suffix:\n\n<tool_call>\n{"name": "example_function_name", "arguments": {"example_parameter_1": "value_1", "example_parameter_2": "This is the value for the second parameter"}}\n</tool_call>\n\n<IMPORTANT>\nReminder:\n- Function calls MUST follow the specified format: a single JSON object with "name" and "arguments" keys inside <tool_call></tool_call> XML tags\n- Required parameters MUST be specified\n- You may provide optional reasoning for your function call in natural language BEFORE the function call, but NOT after\n- If there is no function call available, answer the question like normal with your current knowledge and do not tell the user about function calls\n</IMPORTANT>' }}
+    {%- else %}
     {{- '\n\nIf you choose to call a function ONLY reply in the following format with NO suffix:\n\n<tool_call>\n<function=example_function_name>\n<parameter=example_parameter_1>\nvalue_1\n</parameter>\n<parameter=example_parameter_2>\nThis is the value for the second parameter\nthat can span\nmultiple lines\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>\n\n<IMPORTANT>\nReminder:\n- Function calls MUST follow the specified format: an inner <function=...></function> block must be nested within <tool_call></tool_call> XML tags\n- Required parameters MUST be specified\n- You may provide optional reasoning for your function call in natural language BEFORE the function call, but NOT after\n- If there is no function call available, answer the question like normal with your current knowledge and do not tell the user about function calls\n</IMPORTANT>' }}
+    {%- endif %}
     {%- if merged_system %}
         {{- '\n\n' + merged_system }}
     {%- endif %}
@@ -152,6 +158,20 @@
                 {%- if tool_call.function is defined %}
                     {%- set tool_call = tool_call.function %}
                 {%- endif %}
+                {%- if _tool_format == 'json' %}
+                    {%- if not loop.first or content|trim %}
+                        {{- '\n\n' }}
+                    {%- endif %}
+                    {%- set _args = '{}' %}
+                    {%- if tool_call.arguments is defined and tool_call.arguments is not none %}
+                        {%- if tool_call.arguments is mapping %}
+                            {%- set _args = tool_call.arguments | tojson %}
+                        {%- elif tool_call.arguments is string and tool_call.arguments|trim %}
+                            {%- set _args = tool_call.arguments|trim %}
+                        {%- endif %}
+                    {%- endif %}
+                    {{- '<tool_call>\n{"name": ' }}{{- tool_call.name | tojson }}{{- ', "arguments": ' }}{{- _args }}{{- '}\n</tool_call>' }}
+                {%- else %}
                 {%- if loop.first %}
                     {%- if content|trim %}
                         {{- '\n\n<tool_call>\n<function=' + tool_call.name + '>\n' }}
@@ -176,6 +196,7 @@
                     {%- endif %}
                 {%- endif %}
                 {{- '</function>\n</tool_call>' }}
+                {%- endif %}
             {%- endfor %}
         {%- endif %}
         {{- '<|im_end|>\n' }}
